22/12/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The daily <I>Utrinski Vesnik</I> reports Monday (22 December) that the government will implement its action plan to boost employment in March. 
Citing Labour and Social Policy Minister Jovan Manasievski as its source, the newspaper says cabinet ministers are discussing final details with EU experts and representatives of trade unions and employers' organisations.
In other news, Parliament Speaker Ljupco Jordanovski says he wants to see changes in parliamentary rules, aimed at improving efficiency. 
In an interview Sunday with Radio Free Europe, he said lawmakers would spend the beginning of the new year focused on the decentralisation package. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 22/12/03; MIA, A1 TV - 21/12/03)
